Attending the Acute Leukemia Forum (#ALF14) in SF today. Will try to tweet a bit, tho probably lightly since wifi is a bit sketchy. #leusm
#ALF14 #leusm: Grupp: limitatn of T cell tx for acute leuk is the need for effector Ts to expand by logs; hasn't happened in most studies.
#ALF14 #leusm: Grupp: modern CARTs achieve massive Ag-driven prolif, in some pts. If you can't find the cells by flow, pt will not respond.
#ALF14 #leusm Grupp: Severe cytokine release syndrome w CARTs typified by extremely high levels of IL-6, as well as IFNg, sCD25, and GM-CSF.
#ALF14 #leusm Grupp: 3 patients at CHOP treated with CD19-targeted CARTs have relapsed with CD19 neg disease clones.
#ALF14 #leusm Grupp: interestingly, have seen some responses in patients who failed blinatumomab using CD19 CARTs.
#ALF14 #leusm Grupp: Treating CART induced severe cytokine release syndr w tocilizumab does not appear to decr T cell expansion or efficacy
RT @hemedoc: #ALF14 #leusm Grupp: Treating CART induced severe cytokine release syndr w tocilizumab does not appear to decr T cell expansio…
#ALF14 #leusm Majeti: TCGA survey of 200 AML genomes shows ~5 coding mutations in potential driver genes per clone.
#ALF14 #leusm Majeti: Pre-leukemic clones accum in (and freq become dominant in) phenotypically nrml HSC compartment prior to AML emergence
#ALF14 #leusm Majeti: "Founder" mutations occur in pre-leuk in landscaping genes (DNMT3a, IDH) and then in prolif genes (FLT3, NPM1, Ras).
#ALF14 #leusm Majeti: Relapse may derive from evol of the leuk clone, selection of a chemo resist clone, or more muts on pre-leuk background
#ALF14 #leusm Estey: how to use day 14 marrow? In 4 SWOG trials, CR after 2nd 3+7 for persist dz was 44%, but only 50% recd 2nd course.
#ALF14 #leusm Estey: Don't predict response to 2nd 3+7: blasts percentage, day of "day 14" marrow, day of starting 2nd course.
#ALF14 #leusm Estey: still need to identify best predictors of who will respond to the salvage course vs who should receive something else
#ALF14 #leusm Estey: that something else could be course of HDAC with HCT in aplasia (Stoelzel et al, Leukemia 2013, 27:2068.)
